HEADWORD: Suspiration
<hw>Sus`pi*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>suspiratio</ets>. See <er>Suspire</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of
sighing, or fetching a long and deep breath; a deep respiration; a
sigh.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Windy <qex>suspiration</qex> of forced breath.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suspire</ent>⟦br⟧
